President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Iowa and authorized federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts following severe storms, tornadoes, straight-line winds, and flooding that occurred from June 6 to July 2, 2018. The federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures statewide. Timothy J. Scranton has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.